   "body" : "When I send a small transaction (< 0.5 BTC, for me at least; I don't know where the actual line is), the BitCoin client pops up a warning that says that I'm \"over the size limit.\" As I understand it, the fee is imposed for *very small* transactions (which makes sense, as I've sent large transfers before and not seen it)-- so the string should probably be changed.\r\n\r\nEdit: looking more at the code, since it can be both over *and* under the size limit and trigger that error, it's more complex; I'll work on a rewording and submit a pull request when I have one.",
